2. Normalisation des donnes :

# Create a function to normalize data:
normalization <- function(dataframe) {
  Counts = round(data.frame(dataframe[,-1], row.names = dataframe[,1]))
  pseudoCounts <- log2(Counts+1)
  dgeCounts <- DGEList(Counts)

  # We normalize the data in order to take into account the different overall number of reads between samples
  dgeCounts <- calcNormFactors(dgeCounts, method="TMM")
  eff.lib.size <- dgeCounts$samples$lib.size*dgeCounts$samples$norm.factors
  normCounts <- sweep(dgeCounts$counts, 2, eff.lib.size, "/")*10^6
  
  # which is equivalent to normCounts <- cpm(dgeFull)
  pseudoNormCounts <- log2(normCounts + 1)
  df_norm = data.frame(pseudoNormCounts)
  df_norm = cbind(gene_id = rownames(df_norm), df_norm, row.names = NULL)
  return(df_norm)
}

# Apply the normalize function on data:
df_linear_norm = normalization(dataframe = df_linear)
df_circrna_norm = normalization(dataframe = df_circrna)
df_readc_norm = normalization(dataframe = df_readcount)

4. Rgression linaire (nuage de points) :

ggp <- function(dataframe, title) {
  dataframe$col = as.factor(as.vector(unlist(lapply(dataframe$circ, function(x){if(is.na(x)){"no circ"} else{"circ"}}))))
ggplot(dataframe, aes(x=as.numeric(linear), y=as.numeric(readc))) +
  geom_point(aes(x=as.numeric(linear), y=as.numeric(readc), color = col)) +
  geom_smooth(method=lm, se=FALSE, fullrange=TRUE, aes(x=as.numeric(linear), y=as.numeric(readc)), colour="dodgerblue2") +
  geom_point(data = subset(dataframe, col == 'circ'), aes(x=as.numeric(linear), y=as.numeric(readc), color = col)) +
  geom_smooth(method=lm, se=FALSE, fullrange=TRUE, data = subset(dataframe, col == 'circ'), aes(x=as.numeric(linear), y=as.numeric(readc)), colour="saddlebrown") +
  labs(title=title, x = "TotalRNAseq expression level (read count/gene norm)",
                    y = "mRNAseq expression level (read count/gene norm)") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5), legend.position="bottom") +
  scale_color_manual(values=c('saddlebrown', 'dodgerblue2'), name="Genes",
                     labels=c("Involved in the production of circRNA", "Not involved in the production of circRNA")) +
  stat_fit_glance(data = subset(dataframe, col == 'no circ'), colour="dodgerblue2",
                  method = "lm", label.x = "left", label.y = 1, size=3.5,
                  method.args = list(formula = y ~ x),
                  mapping = aes(label = sprintf('r^2~"="~%.3f', stat(r.squared))), parse = TRUE) +
  stat_fit_glance(data = subset(dataframe, col == 'circ'), colour="saddlebrown",
                  method = "lm", label.x = "left", label.y = "top", size=3.5,
                  method.args = list(formula = y ~ x),
                  mapping = aes(label = sprintf('r^2~"="~%.3f', stat(r.squared))), parse = TRUE)
}

ggp_1 = ggp(dataframe = df_ssc_1, "ssc_testis_1 (31)")
ggp_2 = ggp(dataframe = df_ssc_2, "ssc_testis_2 (05)")
ggp_3 = ggp(dataframe = df_ssc_3, "ssc_testis_3 (54)")

suppressWarnings(suppressMessages(grid.arrange(ggp_1, ggp_2, ggp_3, ncol = 2, nrow = 2)))
